p: The calendered electrodes show good rate capability, as presented in Figure 11. The C/SiO 2-0.085 M composite’s calendered electrode shows the best rate performance (1231.3 mAh·g −1, coulombic efficiency (CE) = 99.7% at C/10 and 922.2 mAh·g −1, CE = 99.5% at 1C). An increasing capacity when increasing the carbon content can be noticed, which is in agreement with other results from literature. The capacity decreases at higher C rate; however, a higher specific capacity could be obtained when returned to C/10, indicating that the capacity decrease at high C rates is reversible.
